            Message(text: "Historians differ in their assessment of the impact of the Antonine Plague on Rome. To some, the plague was the beginning of the decline of the Roman Empire. To others, it was a minor event, documented by Galen and other writers but only slightly more deadly than other epidemics which frequently ravaged parts of the empire."),
            Message(text: "Only two of emperor Marcus Aurelius' fourteen children are known to have reached adulthood."),
